								<div itemprop="articleBody">
		<p><img style="display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;" src="https://cs.kku.ac.th/images/news/2563/30_toi2020_close/128124722_225454905641534_5488970032101915505_o.jpg" alt="" width="564" height="376" /></p>
 
<p style="font-weight: 400; text-align: center;"> </p>
<p style="font-weight: 400; text-align: center;"><b><strong>16th Thailand Olympiad in Informatics : 16th TOI</strong></b></p>
<p style="font-weight: 400;"> </p>
<p style="font-weight: 400;">                    On Tuesday, December 1, 2020, at 9:00 a.m. at Wittayavipas Conference Room 1, Wittayavipas Building. Faculty of Science Khon Kaen University Assistant Professor Dr. Somkiat Srijaranai, Dean of the Faculty of Science. Khon Kaen University President of the Academic Olympic Center, Khon Kaen University Than in the closing ceremony of the competition Khon Kaen University's name We would like to express our appreciation for the responsibility of every student. That is well prepared and practiced in programming skills To be academically ready For this competition For successful students And in competitive examinations Awarded gold, silver, bronze medals and honors announced. It's an honor And the pride of the parents, teachers, and faculty members of the resort center who have devoted their whole body The strength in the transfer of knowledge and training are well. The competition will have both those who are fulfilled and missed, but more importantly, we have the opportunity to act as a representative of friends from the resort center to join this activity. Have a chance to meet new friends Gain experience and academic knowledge I hope that we will bring these good things. Go broadcast and practice, learn more. To bring the knowledge that we have to cooperate to help develop the country in the future</p>
<p style="font-weight: 400; text-align: left;"> </p>
<p style="font-weight: 400; text-align: center;"><img src="https://cs.kku.ac.th/images/news/2563/30_toi2020_close/127580628_225455225641502_3066979690215729588_o.jpg" alt="" width="338" height="225" /><img src="https://cs.kku.ac.th/images/news/2563/30_toi2020_close/128304230_225446662309025_7540681785040082753_o.jpg" alt="" width="338" height="225" /></p>
<p style="font-weight: 400; text-align: center;"> </p>
<p style="font-weight: 400;">                  Associate Professor Dr. Siraphat Chianwattana The chairman of the organizing committee for the 16th National Computer Olympics said a summary report of the competition that, on behalf of the Chairman of the Committee for organizing the 16th National Computer Olympics, he was very happy and thankful to everyone That honors joining in this event Management of the 16th Academic Olympiad computer competition, the Resort Foundation has assigned Computer Science Faculty of Science Khon Kaen University Host an event This competition. Has begun to operate from 28 November to 1 December 2020 with good cooperation from the government and private sectors. We would like to thank you very much for this opportunity for the student competition activities. It is the organization of computer programming competition to solve problems in numerical calculation. Computer science And related fields Based on the constitution of the National Computer Olympics There are 2 rounds of the exam. The exam is quite difficult. Candidates must have proficiency in programming and solving computer-based problems. The 16th National Computer Olympiad had a total of 93 students participating in the competition, 90 of whom were representative students of 13 POS centers nationwide and 3 students from the IPST. Also has an advisory board Expert Academic Committee Center faculty members from various institutions, including team leaders Deputy Team Leader Observation teacher, And the organizing committee to organize competitions to participate more than 300 people</p>
<p>As a result of the 16th National Computer Olympiad in 2020, 45 people were awarded gold, silver, and bronze medals.</p>
<p>- Gold medal award,         8 people</p>
<p>- Silver medal award for   15 people</p>
<p>- Bronze award level        22 people</p>
<p style="font-weight: 400;"> </p>
<p>There is also a special award honored by the Siam Commercial Bank Public Company Limited and the Science Foundation. Dr. Preecha-Prapai Amatayakun supports the prize fund for the 2020 Academic Computer Olympiad, consisting of</p>
<p>- 1st highest score award With prize money of 6,000 baht</p>
<p>2 prizes</p>
<p>- Second highest score award With prize money of 4,000 baht</p>
<p>Since there are two highest-scoring awards, first and second-place rewards are combined.</p>
<p>- Third highest score award With prize money of 3,000 baht</p>
<p>1 prize</p>
<p>- Regional high score award By each region</p>
<p>Will receive a prize of 1,000 baht per prize, a total of 4 prizes</p>
<p>- A special prize with a prize of 5,000 baht by judging from the response process and the method that the jury deems appropriate for the special prize.</p>
<p style="font-weight: 400;"> </p>
<p style="font-weight: 400;">On this occasion, congratulations, and congratulations. In the knowledge and abilities of everyone For those who did not receive this award, Everyone has demonstrated their full academic potential. We are encouraged to develop a great experience. This competition cannot be achieved without cooperation and assistance. Support from all parties On this occasion, I would like to thank the POW Foundation, the academic committees from every institution, the faculty, each student staff, every resort center, the competition committee. As well as agencies in both the public and private sectors That supports and makes this competition successful as well</p>
<p style="font-weight: 400; text-align: center;"> </p>
<p style="font-weight: 400; text-align: center;"><img src="https://cs.kku.ac.th/images/news/2563/30_toi2020_close/127819082_225446825642342_6407979029583222426_o.jpg" alt="" width="539" height="359" /></p>	</div>

	
